snippet.description:
The cougar (or mountain lion) diorama depicts the Grand Canyon, which was declared a national monument in 1908 by President Theodore Roosevelt, a lifelong friend and supporter of the Museum and its mission of conservation. The recent restoration of the diorama included the addition of whiskers to the two large cats.

The restored Hall of North American Mammals reopened October 2012.

snippet.title: Cougars Get New Whiskers

snippet.description:
Three male cougars hiss, growl and chew during feeding; a female cougar hisses and growls during mating. Recorded in Alberta, Canada in 1979 and 1966, respectively.

Audio recording courtesy of the Maccaulay Library at the Cornell Lab of Ornithology, Ithaca, New York. Recordist: Geoffrey A. Keller.
